    "long_instructions": "#### Let’s start by learning a bit more about what Object Oriented Languages can do.   \r\n\r\n### **As you watch this video, consider:**\r\n\r\n- #### How is object oriented programming different from or similar to other programming languages you may have experience with?\r\n\r\n#### Note that this video shows how to write your own class. You will be writing your own classes in your workshops this summer. \r\n\r\n#### In this module we will focus on using a class in Code.org called the `Painter` class, not writing classes. \r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n#### **Up next:** We will look at our first program that uses the `Painter` class."
